<HL>
   M/A-Com's MAC Unit Sale
</HL>
<DATE>
04/18/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION
</SO>
<CO>
   MAI
</CO>
<IN>
TENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM)
</IN>
<LP>
   BURLINGTON, Mass. -- M/A-Com Inc. said it reached an
agreement to sell its MAC division to Microwave Radio Corp.
of Lowell, Mass., as part of a previously announced
restructuring program.
   Terms of the cash transaction weren't disclosed.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   The maker of semiconductors and parts used in
telecommunications, radar and electronic warfare said the
division, which makes radio communications systems, had
fiscal 1989 sales of about $19 million.
   The company said it expects to complete the sale by the
end of the month.
   Microwave Radio makes portable microwave radios for
electronic news gathering.
</TEXT>
